## Review summary

The Brave adapter (`brave.ts`) is well-written: it closely mirrors the existing Google adapter's structure, uses a proper type-narrowing filter predicate instead of unsafe casts, handles the missing-`web`-block edge case, and has thorough test coverage (enablement, component support, request shape, result mapping, github-link detection, filtering, error propagation). The config, registry, ranking-weight, and type-union additions are all correct and consistent.

## Change made

**Extracted the duplicated `githubUrlOf` helper.** The new `brave.ts` copied `google.ts`'s `githubUrlOf` function verbatim — the same try/catch URL-hostname check appeared in two places. I moved it to a shared `src/lib/adapters/github-url.ts` module and imported it in both adapters. This removes the duplication so the github-detection logic has a single source of truth, with no change in behavior.

## Verification

- `npm run typecheck` passes.
- All adapter tests pass except a **pre-existing** `smithery.test.ts` failure, which I confirmed (via `git stash`) fails independently of my changes — the Smithery adapter was disabled in earlier commits and is out of scope for this branch.

